 {"id":"bd-10y0","title":"Migrate input widgets with cursor control (Category C)","description":"## Scope

Migrate Category C widgets - input widgets that need cursor positioning.

## Frame Features Used

- `frame.cursor_position` - Set where the cursor should appear
- `frame.cursor_visible` - Control cursor visibility

## Migration Pattern

1. Change signature to use Frame
2. Set cursor position for text inputs:
   ```rust
   fn render(&self, area: Rect, frame: &mut Frame) {
       let buf = &mut frame.buffer;

       // ... draw the input widget ...

       // Position cursor at current input position
       if self.focused {
           let cursor_x = area.x + self.cursor_offset as u16;
           let cursor_y = area.y;
           frame.cursor_position = Some((cursor_x, cursor_y));
           frame.cursor_visible = true;
       }
   }
   ```

## Widgets Expected in This Category

Based on functionality (to be confirmed by audit):
- TextInput
- MultilineInput (if exists)
- SearchBox (if exists)
- Any editable text field

## Critical Considerations

1. **Focus state**: Only set cursor when widget is focused
2. **Cursor position math**: Must account for:
   - Area offset (area.x, area.y)
   - Text scroll offset
   - Unicode character widths
3. **Cursor visibility**: May need to hide cursor for password fields or inactive states

## Important

This is the most critical category - broken cursor positioning makes inputs unusable.
Test thoroughly with real terminal interaction.

